=head1 DESCRIPTION

A structure that is used to specify testing a connection to a service.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AuthenticationConfiguration => L<Paws::Glue::AuthenticationConfigurationInput>

A structure containing the authentication configuration in the
TestConnection request. Required for a connection to Salesforce using
OAuth authentication.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ConnectionProperties => L<Paws::Glue::ConnectionProperties>

The key-value pairs that define parameters for the connection.

JDBC connections use the following connection properties:

=over

=item *

Required: All of (C<HOST>, C<PORT>, C<JDBC_ENGINE>) or
C<JDBC_CONNECTION_URL>.

=item *

Required: All of (C<USERNAME>, C<PASSWORD>) or C<SECRET_ID>.

=item *

Optional: C<JDBC_ENFORCE_SSL>, C<CUSTOM_JDBC_CERT>,
C<CUSTOM_JDBC_CERT_STRING>, C<SKIP_CUSTOM_JDBC_CERT_VALIDATION>. These
parameters are used to configure SSL with JDBC.

=back

SALESFORCE connections require the C<AuthenticationConfiguration>
member to be configured.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ConnectionType => Str

The type of connection to test. This operation is only available for
the C<JDBC> or C<SALESFORCE> connection types.



